.TH "sys_open_by_handle_at" 9 "sys_open_by_handle_at" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sys_open_by_handle_at \- Open the file handle
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "long" sys_open_by_handle_at
.BI "(int mountdirfd "  ","
.BI "struct file_handle __user * handle "  ","
.BI "int flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mountdirfd" 12
directory file descriptor
.IP "handle" 12
file handle to be opened
.IP "flags" 12
open flags.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fImountdirfd\fP indicate the directory file descriptor
of the mount point. file handle is decoded relative
to the vfsmount pointed by the \fImountdirfd\fP. \fIflags\fP
value is same as the open(2) flags.
